JOHANNESBURG - Demonstrators tried to disrupt the City of Joburg's Integrated Development Plan meeting for a second night on Wednesday.They prevented Mayor Herman Mashaba from speaking; on Tuesday night ANC members did the same.Johannesburg Metro Police broke up a scuffle.READ: Mashaba to lay charges against ANC councillors after violent meetingMashaba said he was disappointed by the conduct of his opposition."I think last night as they started doing what I saw with the former minister of finance, just causing disruptions not allowing anyone to speak."I think it is quite unfortunate that the ANC is not allowing communities to engage with the government. It is why they got voted out of power."It's the last kicks of a dying horse, but if you decide to kill the ANC don't allow our country to go down with you," said Mashaba.eNCA